div.p:
—He had led Labor Party for 13 years, 8 of them as Prime Minister, longer
                            than any peacetime predecessor this century, and served on the Front
                            Bench nearly 30 years;

—Wilson’s closest confidants, in
                            addition to Queen, have been aware for several months of his intention
                            to resign near his sixtieth birthday;

—Best explanation for resignation is the simplest, i.e., Wilson’s own publicly announced
                            reasons; recent left-wing revolt, if it had any effect, merely delayed
                            announcement a few days;
